    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-19T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="647"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d647">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/7–1944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-19T22:00:00+01:00"
                            >July 19, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [ReceivedJuly 19—12:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4604. Your 1945, June 6; my 4260, July 5.<note n="24" xml:id="d647fn24">Neither
                        printed.</note> Foreign Office note dated yesterday states according
                    telegram from Swiss Legation, Budapest, Hungarian Government has authorized
                    departure from Hungary all Jews in possession entry permit for another country,
                    including Palestine.<note n="25" xml:id="d647fn25">For original statement on
                        Hungarian offer made public in Switzerland by the Intercross on July 18, see
                        circular telegram of August 18, <ref target="#pg_1127">p. 1127</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>According same message German Government will permit transit through occupied
                    territories. Necessary measures for evacuation will <pb facs="1114" n="1100"
                        xml:id="pg_1100"/> be taken soon as possible by Swiss Legation in
                    collaboration with Palestinian Bureau, Budapest. Travel documents will probably
                    be Hungarian police passports.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
